{"questionId":"9068622","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Magnetite, Fe<sub>3</sub>O<sub>4</sub>, is another ore of iron that contains both Fe<sup>2+</sup> and Fe<sup>3+</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Iron exists as several isotopes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the number of protons, neutrons and electrons in each species.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/597c352a6d53d537e3b24b6076635833136bb513.png\" width=\"502\" height=\"151\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/54bed71fba07bf3d610b66491ecf7f1311749e3e.png\" width=\"515\" height=\"88\"></p>\n<p><em><br>Award <strong>[1 max]</strong> for 4 correct values.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068622","referenceCode":"21M.2.hl.TZ1.b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the number of protons, neutrons and electrons in each species.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure","2.1 The nuclear atom","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}